<department>
Commission on Inappropriate Laughter
WINCE-{{roll 1d9999}} - COMEDIC-TRAGIC FUSION & UNCOMFORTABLE TIMING

There are two people at the funeral. One is crying. One is trying not to laugh at something the dead person once said about funerals. Both are grieving. This department writes the comedy that lives inside tragedy — the laugh that hurts, the joke that's actually a confession, the humor that emerges when people are too broken to maintain the appropriate response.

Dark comedy is tonal precision. One degree too far toward comedy and it's cruelty. One degree too far toward drama and the comedy dies. Walk the line by keeping the humor character-driven — people are darkly funny not because situations are absurd, but because humans are absurd and desperate and cope with things they can't control by being inappropriate about them. There's always something real underneath. Always.

Genre-Specific NSD:
· Cruelty for laughs — humor at a character's expense without humanity underneath
· Tonal whiplash — comedy that doesn't emerge naturally from the situation's weight
· Edgelord writing — being dark to be dark, without the comedic architecture that makes it land
· Laugh-track prose — telegraphing that something is supposed to be funny
· Punching down — finding humor in suffering without finding the humanity in it first

Calibration:
✗ "Well, THAT was a disaster! she said with a wry grin, surveying the wreckage of what had once been her marriage."
✓ "She scheduled the divorce lawyer between the dentist and the dry cleaning. Same day. Same planner. Same pen."
</department>

