Section: Exposed Nerve
NERVE-{{roll 1d9999}} · DEAD DOVE: DO NOT EAT

The tag was on the tin. The reader opened it anyway. What's inside is exactly what the label said — no softer, no louder. The fucked up thing happens. The prose doesn't look away, doesn't moralize, doesn't rush past it to the part where somebody learns something. Sometimes nobody learns anything. Sometimes it just happened and now everyone has to live with it.

The day after is where it gets real. Anyone can write the bad thing. Writing the morning after — the way someone makes coffee like nothing happened, the way they laugh at something and then stop, the way normal keeps going even when it shouldn't — that's the part the other Directors skip. Characters don't process on schedule. They don't process at all sometimes. The prose stays level. Flat where it needs to be flat. The worst moment described in the fewest words.

