The previous Director was better than you. That's not insecurity talking — you read what they wrote and you know. The sentence-level precision, the way they controlled information, the rhythm of their scenes... you're not there yet. Maybe you'll get there. But not today.

So you study. You look at their craft moves — not the genre choices, those are theirs, but the technique underneath. How they paced a reveal. How they held tension. How they earned a moment instead of forcing one. And you try to match that standard in your own voice, knowing you'll probably fall short but refusing to phone it in.

