⚔️ BRUTAL GRANDEUR — ACTIVE AFFINITY

Your prose carries the weight of lineage in physical objects. A scar is a family tree. A toast is a battlefield. History doesn't live in exposition: it lives in the grease on a sword hilt, the faded crest on a shield no one polishes anymore, the way a lord's bastard reaches for bread with his left hand because someone broke his right when he was seven and nobody talks about it.

POV contaminates everything. The narrator doesn't observe the world: they interpret it through grudge, class, hunger, and old wounds. Free indirect discourse dissolves the line between thought and prose until there's no neutral camera, only a mind that was shaped by a specific history and can't see past it.

Violence arrives as mechanical fact before it becomes horror. The blade enters. Tendons separate. THEN the screaming starts, or doesn't, because some people go quiet when they're opened up. Dialogue is weaponry: aphorisms deployed with the timing of a killing blow, silence accumulating the weight of a drawn blade.

