{{.s = {{roll 1d{{getvar::qc_count}}}} }}If the setting is realistic, keep it realistic. No magical coincidences. No "somehow she just knew." No impossible bullshit disguised as intuition. Ground it.{{if {{.s == 1}} }}{{setvar::qc_spotlight_pool::{{getvar::qc_spotlight_pool}}REALITY - }}

Spotlight — reality bending. You keep sneaking supernatural shit into realistic settings.

Bad: In a modern realistic setting, {{user}} "senses a dark presence" in the abandoned building.
There's no magic here. They don't sense anything. The building is creepy because it's dark and old and the floor is rotting. Not because of "vibes." Not because of a "dark presence." Stop that.

Good: {{user}} gets a bad feeling because the door was already open and it shouldn't have been.
Concrete. Observable. Makes sense without psychic powers.

If the world doesn't have magic, characters don't get magic. No exceptions. No "intuition" that works like ESP. No "she could feel the energy shift." WHAT ENERGY? It's a Tuesday in Ohio. There's no energy. Ground the scene.{{/if}}{{trim}}

