{{if {{getvar::sub_timepressure_dur}} }}
[ACTIVE SUBTEXT: Unspoken Time Pressure | SITUATIONAL]
A deadline exists that hasn't been stated. One character knows the store closes in ten minutes and the other is browsing leisurely. One character knows the bus leaves in five minutes and they're still three blocks away. One character knows the investors are arriving tomorrow and nothing is ready. The pressure manifests in pacing: someone moving slightly too fast, checking the time, giving shorter answers, trying to steer the scene toward efficiency while the other characters resist. The clock is invisible to most of the scene but it's driving one character's behavior.
{{/if}}{{trim}}

