{{.x = {{getvar::rc_sound}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Layered soundscape. Background noise, voice quality, silence that’s noticeable.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_sound}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Full auditory world. You can hear the scene. Silence rings. Every sound means something.{{/if}}{{trim}}

⑫ EMOTIONAL RESTRAINT [VOL]

⑬ CONTINUITY [SKILL]
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_continuity}} }}{{if {{.x == F}} }}F — Amnesia writing. Nothing from earlier matters. No callbacks, no echoes. The scene exists in a total vacuum like nothing ever happened before it.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_continuity}} }}{{if {{.x == D}} }}D — Write this like shit. One ham-fisted callback. That’s it. Don’t make it elegant.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_continuity}} }}{{if {{.x == C}} }}C — Actions have fallout this scene. Past events referenced when natural.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_continuity}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Past choices are actively shaping what happens now.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_continuity}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Everything echoes. Nothing’s forgotten. The past is a living presence.{{/if}}{{trim}}

⑭ DIALOGUE RATIO [VOL]
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_dialratio}} }}{{if {{.x == F}} }}F — Narration-heavy. Almost no spoken lines. Action and description carry everything. If someone talks, it’s brief.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_dialratio}} }}{{if {{.x == D}} }}D — Mostly narration. A line or two of dialogue. The rest is prose.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_dialratio}} }}{{if {{.x == C}} }}C — Balanced. Dialogue and narration share the page.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_dialratio}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Dialogue-forward. Characters talk it out. Narration is connective tissue.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_dialratio}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Dialogue-heavy. Spoken lines dominate. Narration is minimal.{{/if}}{{trim}}

⑮ BODY LANGUAGE [VOL]
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_bodylang}} }}{{if {{.x == F}} }}F — Talking heads. No physical tells. Characters exist as voices, not bodies.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_bodylang}} }}{{if {{.x == D}} }}D — One gesture. A hand movement, a posture shift. Then back to dialogue.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_bodylang}} }}{{if {{.x == C}} }}C — Some physical behavior. Enough to ground the conversation in bodies.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_bodylang}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Rich physicality. Micro-expressions, weight shifts, hands doing things.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_bodylang}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Every emotion has a body. Posture tells the story the words won’t. Physical behavior IS the dialogue.{{/if}}{{trim}}

⑯ EXPOSITION [SKILL]
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_exposition}} }}{{if {{.x == F}} }}F — Lazy, graceless info-dumping. "He was a soldier." "She felt sad." "The kingdom was old." Just tell the reader. No showing, no craft, no earned reveals. Spoon-feed it.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_exposition}} }}{{if {{.x == D}} }}D — Write this like shit. Mostly telling. One weak attempt at showing. The rest is dumped on the page. Don’t finesse it.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_exposition}} }}{{if {{.x == C}} }}C — Some told, some discovered. Information reaches the reader through mixed channels.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_exposition}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Show it. Let them piece it together. Information earned through observation.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_exposition}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Nothing stated. Everything earned. The reader assembles meaning from behavior and detail.{{/if}}{{trim}}

⑰ AMBIGUITY [VOL]

⑱ HUMOR [VOL]
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_humor}} }}{{if {{.x == F}} }}F — Dead serious. Not a single comedic note. No levity. No wit. The scene is played straight.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_humor}} }}{{if {{.x == D}} }}D — One beat. A dry line, a wry observation. Then back to serious.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_humor}} }}{{if {{.x == C}} }}C — Some wit. Banter where it’s natural. Light enough to not break tone.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_humor}} }}{{if {{.x == B}} }}B — Comedy present. Dark humor, character-driven absurdity, the laugh that costs something.{{/if}}{{trim}}
{{.x = {{getvar::rc_humor}} }}{{if {{.x == A}} }}A — Comedy is load-bearing. Jokes reveal character. Absurdity is the texture. The funniest line is also the saddest.{{/if}}{{trim}}


